summary: One thing I love about critical role that TAZ doesn’t have is being able to see faces. The cast are all voice actors but they’re...
body: One thing I love about critical role that TAZ doesn’t have is being able to see faces. The cast are all voice actors but they’re all so immersed in their characters that watching Liam’s face while Matt narrates Caleb’s dream or just being able to see everyone else’s reactions as something goes down is Amazing. TAZ gives you this incredible nuance from what you hear only— we always talk about that little shudder in Travis’ breath when the chalice makes its offer— but seeing faces really takes it to another level and I LOVE it.
